theorem P3_iff_isOpen_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P3 A ↔ IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hP3
    have h₁ : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := hP3
    have h_closure : closure (A : Set X) = A := hA_closed.closure_eq
    have h₂ : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (A : Set X) := by
      simpa [h_closure] using h₁
    have h_eq : (A : Set X) = interior (A : Set X) := by
      apply Set.Subset.antisymm h₂
      exact interior_subset
    simpa [h_eq] using isOpen_interior
  · intro hOpen
    exact Topology.P3_of_isOpen (A := A) hOpen

set_option maxRecDepth 10000

theorem closure_subset_closure_interior_of_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (A : Set X) →
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := by
  intro hA
  -- From `P3` we obtain `A ⊆ interior (closure A)`, hence
  -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h₁ : closure (A : Set X) ⊆
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
    have : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := hA
    exact closure_minimal this isClosed_closure
  -- Conversely, `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A`, so taking closures yields
  -- `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₂ : closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆
      closure (A : Set X) :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset (s := closure (A : Set X)))
  -- Hence the two closures coincide.
  have hEq : closure (A : Set X) =
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) :=
    Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂
  -- Using this equality together with monotonicity of `closure` we obtain the result.
  simpa [hEq] using
    closure_mono (interior_subset_interior_closure (A := A))

theorem interior_closure_inter_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X)) ⊆
      interior (closure (A : Set X)) ∩ interior (closure (B : Set X)) := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    have h_subset : closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
      apply closure_mono
      exact Set.inter_subset_left
    exact (interior_mono h_subset) hx
  have hxB : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure (B : Set X)) := by
    have h_subset : closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X) ⊆ closure (B : Set X) := by
      apply closure_mono
      exact Set.inter_subset_right
    exact (interior_mono h_subset) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB
